title: COLLEGE SPORTS: SHU women's soccer edges Concordia
text: COLLEGE SPORTS: SHU women's soccer edges Concordia Comment The Daily Telegram - Adrian, MI By Daily Telegram staff Posted Oct. 8, 2015 at 12:00 PM By Daily Telegram staff Posted Oct. 8, 2015 at 12:00 PM ANN ARBOR A late goal by Taylor Mulder lifted the NAIA15th-ranked Siena Heights University women's soccer team to a 1-0 victory over Wolverine-Hoosier Athletic Conference foe Concordia on Wednesday. The Saints and Cardinals were tied going in to halftime with Concordia outshooting Siena Heights 7-3 in the first half. Mulder scored the game-winner for the Saints in the 87th minute, finishing a through ball from Samantha Bartelotti. Meghan Bogg made five saves and earned the win in net for the Saints. Siena Heights was outshot by the Cardinals, 13-11. Concordia (8-4-1, 4-1 WHAC) also held a 7-2 corner-kick advantage. The Saints (10-2-0, 3-1 WHAC) will be back in action Saturday against Lawrence Tech at 7 p.m. Adrian 0, Olivet 0: At Adrian, the Bulldogs played to their sixth scoreless tie of the season in Wednesday's Michigan Intercollegiate Athletic Association match. Adrian (3-4-6, 1-4-4 MIAA) limited Olivet (8-3-1, 5-3-1) to four shots on goal in the contest. The Bulldogs outshot the Comets 16-8 in regulation. Bulldogs goalkeeper Lexi Lewandowski made four saves for her ninth shutout of the season. Adrian will host MIAA rival Hope on Saturday. VOLLEYBALL Siena Heights at Davenport: At Grand Rapids, Siena Heights fell to Davenport, 3-1, in WHAC play Wednesday. Leze Vukaj had 14 kills and three total blocks to lead the Saints, who lost with set scores of 23-25, 25-18, 25-19, 25-23. Abby Whitehead and Ashleigh Shay added 12 kills apiece for SHU (10-6, 6-6 WHAC). Carly Tillotson (Tecumseh)totaled 43 assists. Nicole Morgan finished with 20 digs. SHU will return to action on Wednesday, Oct. 14, as it heads to Northwestern Ohio for a 7 p.m. WHAC matchup. UNOH held a 13-2 corner-kick advantage. The Saints (6-2-2, 1-1-2) will host Lawrence Tech on Saturday at 4:30 p.m. By Daily Telegram staff The Daily Telegram - Adrian, MI By Daily Telegram staff
